properties.NAME: Moola Bulla Basin
properties.DESCR: Sandstone, conglomerate, mudstone, shale; fluvial-lacustrine-marine environment
properties.COMMENTS: Age inferred from lithological similarity to Speewah Group, and position below Kimberley Group.

properties.DESCR: Sandstone, shale, siltstone, quartz wacke
properties.COMMENTS: Age inferred from lithological correlation with Carr Boyd Group
properties.SOURCE: Hassan, L.Y., 2000. Mineral occurrences and exploration potential of the east Kimberley, Geological Survey of Western Australia. Report 74

properties.SOURCE: Glen, R.A., 1990. Formation and inversion of transtensional basins in the western part of the Lachlan Fold Belt, Australia, with emphasis on the Cobar Basin., Journal of Structural Geology 12(5/6)

properties.DESCR: The Bamaga Basin is a small, offshore, frontier intracratonic sag basin in northern Australia that contains about 4500m of undrilled Palaeozoic sediments.

properties.NAME: Collie Basin
properties.DESCR: The Collie Basin is a small, fault-bounded, probable outlier of the Perth Basin which overlies the Yilgarn Craton.  The basin contains considerable coal resources.

properties.COMMENTS: Outlier of the Sydney Basin

properties.NAME: Malita Graben
properties.DESCR: The Malita Graben is a Mesozoic to Cainozoic depocentre of the Bonaparte Basin in offshore northern Australia, containing more than 10 km of siliciclastic non-marine and marine rocks.
properties.OVERVIEW: The Malita Graben is the major part of the elongated northeast-trending graben system subdivided into the Malita and Calder grabens. These graben lie between platform and shelf areas of relatively shallow Precambrian basement covered by Mesozoic and Cain

properties.NAME: Camooweal-Murphy Domain
properties.DESCR: The Camooweal-Murphy Domain of the Mt Isa Orogen comprises the Murphy Tectonic Ridge, flanked to the south by Lawn Hill Platform cover.
properties.OVERVIEW: A large area comprising in the NW the E-trending Murphy Tectonic Ridge composed of Murphy Metamorphics, Cliffdale Volcanics, Westmoreland Conglomerate, Wire Creek Sandstone, Seigal Volcanics, Buddawadda Basalt, Peters Creek Volcanics, flanked to S by Law

properties.SOURCE: Cawood, P.A., Korsch, R.J., 2008. Assembling Australia: Proterozoic building of a continent, Precambrian Research 166(1-4)

properties.NAME: Georgina Basin
properties.DESCR: The frontier large intracratonic Neoproterozoic to Late Devonian Georgina Basin of western Queensland and east central Northern Territory contains up to 5km of marine and nonmarine siliciclastics and carbonates.
properties.COMMENTS: The Toomba Fault on the basin's southern margin was reactivated in the Cenozoic. Strat units updated according to "Geology and mineral resources of the Northern Territory" (in prep., 68235)
properties.OVERVIEW: The intracratonic Neoproterozoic to Late Devonian Georgina Basin is located in western Queensland and east central Northern Territory. It has a maximum sediment thickness of up to 5,000 m in the south (Toko and Dulcie Synclines) and east (Burke River Bel
properties.SOURCE: Dunster, J.N., Kruse, P.D., Duffett, M.L., Ambrose, G.J., 2007. Geology and resource potential of the southern Georgina Basin, Northern Territory Geological Survey, Digital Information Package 007

properties.NAME: Davenport Province
properties.DESCR: Strat units updated according to "Geology and mineral resources of the Northern Territory" (in prep., 68235, to be released in 2013)
properties.COMMENTS: Maximum age is age of youngest detrital zircon in Unimbra Sandstone. Minimum age is age of dolerite sill with same chemistry and deformation history as Kudinga Basalt.
properties.OVERVIEW: Comprises sedimentary and bimodal volcanic sequence about 8 km thick; sedimentary rocks include quartz-rich, lithic, and feldspathic sandstone, conglomerate, siltstone, shale, claystone, and small amounts of carbonate rocks, with stromatolites. Environme
properties.SOURCE: Donnellan, N., 2005. A framework for the Paleoproterozoic geology of the Tennant Region. IN Annual Geoscience Exploration Seminar (AGES) 2005. Record of Abstracts, Northern Territory Geological Survey Record 2005-001

properties.NAME: Carpentaria Basin
properties.DESCR: The Carpentaria Basin is preserved in Northwest Queensland, Gulf of Carpentaria and the Northern Territory between Katherine and Elliott (previously known as Dunmarra Basin). Smaller areas in the north of Arnhem Land, the south of the Litchfield Province

properties.OVERVIEW:

properties.SOURCE: McConachie, B.A., Draper, J.J., 1997. Carpentaria Basin, AGSO Bulletin 240

properties.DESCR: A 'composite [or multiphase] basin composed of discrete ... basin phases reflecting a dynamic tectonic setting' (refid 22538). It is a platform cover sequence of sedimentary and lesser volcanic rocks, 5-15 km thick, and mostly unmetamorphosed.
properties.COMMENTS: Maximum age is on zircon in Bickerton Rhyolite of Groote Eylandt Group (lowermost group). Minimum age is from detrital zircon studies of units overlying Roper Group: Jamison sandstone, Hyafield mudstone.

properties.SOURCE: Rawlings, D.J., 1999. Stratigraphic resolution of a multiphase intracratonic basin system: the McArthur Basin, northern Australia, Australian Journal of Earth Sciences 46(5)

properties.OVERVIEW: The Karumba Basin is a shallow, epicratonic basin superimposed upon the Mesozoic Carpentaria Basin. This large downwarp basin stretches from near Hughenden north to Papua New Guinea, including the seabed of the Gulf of Carpentaria, as well as most of the
properties.SOURCE: Doutch, H.F., 1976. The Karumba Basin, northeastern Australia and southern New Guinea., BMR Journal of Australian Geology and Geophysics  1(2)

properties.NAME: Mount Oxide Domain
properties.DESCR: The Mount Oxide Domain comprises the southern Lawn Hill Platform and contains basement rocks of the Yaringa Metamorphics that are overlain by rocks of the Eastern Creek Volcanics (base), Myally Subgroup, Quilalar and Bigie Formations, Fiery Creek Volcani
properties.OVERVIEW: The Mount Oxide Domains forms the southern part of Lawn Hill Platform and is composed of Yaringa Metamorphics (basement), Eastern Creek Volcanics, Myally Subgroup siliciclastics, Quilalar and Bigie Formations, Fiery Creek Volcanics, Surprise Creek Format
properties.SOURCE: Geological Survey of Queensland, 2011. North-West Queensland mineral and energy province report and data package, Queensland Department of Employment, Economic Development and Innovation 1v

properties.NAME: Broome Platform
properties.DESCR: The Broome Platform represents the NW part of a broad mid-basin platform of shallow basement (<2000 metres) within the Canning Basin.
properties.SOURCE: Kennard, J.M., Jackson, M.J., Romine, K.K., Shaw, R.D., Southgate, P.N., 1994. Depositional sequences and associated Petroleum systems of the Canning Basin, W.A, in Purcell, P.G. & Purcell, R.R. (eds), The sedimentary basins of Western Australia. Procee*

properties.DESCR: Sandstone, siltstone, mudstone, conglomerate, dolostone, felsic volcanic rocks
properties.COMMENTS: Minimum age inferred from lithological correlation with Capricorn Group. Maximum age inferred from age of underlying Wyloo Group.
properties.SOURCE: Cawood, P.A., Tyler, I.M., 2004. Assembling and reactivating the Proterozoic Capricorn Orogen: lithotectonic elements, orogenies, and significance, Precambrian Research 128(3-4)

properties.NAME: Kimberley Basin
properties.DESCR: The Kimberley Basin, which is comprised of the Kimberley Group, is interpreted to have fored as a broad, semi-enclosed shallow marine basin. The Kimberley Group is dominated by sandstone, with lesser siltstone (Elgee Siltstone), and tholeiitic basalt (Ca

properties.SOURCE: Hassan, L.Y., 2004. Mineral occurrences and exploration potential of the west Kimberley., Geological Survey of Western Australia. Report 88

properties.NAME: Northern Carnarvon Basin
properties.DESCR: The Palaeozoic to Recent Northern Carnarvon Basin, Australia's premier hydrocarbon province, lies mainly offshore on the multiple-rifted northwest Australian margin, and contains up to 15 km of Mesozoic clastic deltaic and marine sediments.
properties.OVERVIEW: The Palaeozoic to Recent Northern Carnarvon Basin, is a large, mainly offshore basin on Australia's northwest shelf. It is Australia's premier hydrocarbon province where the majority of deepwater wells (greater than 500 m water depth) have been drilled.
properties.SOURCE: Hocking, R.M., 1988. Regional geology of the northern Carnarvon Basin. IN Purcell P.G. and Purcell R.R. eds - The North West Shelf, Australia., Petroleum Exploration Society of Australia 1v

properties.NAME: Bonaparte Basin
properties.DESCR: The Cambrian to Recent Bonaparte Basin is a large, mainly offshore petroleum-producing basin on the northwestern Australian multiple-rifted margin. It contains up to 15 km of marine-fluvial siliciclastic and carbonate sediments.
properties.COMMENTS: Highly suitable for CO2 storage (Carbon Storage Taskforce, 2010, Australia's Potential for the Geological Storage of CO2, RET, Canberra)

properties.SOURCE: Mory, A.J., 1991. Geology of the offshore Bonaparte Basin, northwestern Australia., Geological Survey of Western Australia. Report 29

properties.DESCR: As defined by Blewett et al. (2012). Basically follows the North Australian Craton as used by Myers et al. (1996). Actual boundaries follow Shaw et al. (1995) and Hoatson et al. (1996).
properties.OVERVIEW: The North Australian Element, from the Kimberley region in the west to Cape York Peninsula in the east, consists of mostly Proterozoic rocks that were cratonised by 1550 Ma (From Blewett et al., 2012 - verbatim).

properties.SOURCE: Wyche, S., 2008. Kalgoorlie, Youanmi and Narryer terranes of the Yilgarn Craton - a field guide., Geological Survey of Western Australia. Record 2008/12

properties.NAME: Mandurah Terrace
properties.DESCR: The Mandurah Terrace is a Late Paleozoic to Cenozoic shelf adjacent to the Vlaming Sub-basin that separates the Dandaragan Trough to the north from the Bunbury Trough to the south, and is bound to the east by the Darling Fault.

properties.NAME: Beermullah Trough
properties.DESCR: The Beermullah Trough is a northwest-trending depocentre in the Perth Basin containing a series of compressional anticlines and a succession of Mesozoic sedimentary rocks which thickens towards the east.

properties.NAME: Dongara Terrace
properties.DESCR: The Dongara Terrace, located in the northern Perth Basin, forms part of a fault-bounded ridge that separates the Abrolhos Sub-basin and the Dandaragan Trough.
properties.COMMENTS: Contains predominantly Carboniferous-Jurassic rocks with a thin Cenozoic cover.

properties.NAME: Central Australian Element
properties.DESCR: As defined by Blewett et al. (2012). Basically follows Myers et al. (1996) though joins their Central Australian Terranes and their Albany-Fraser orogen into the Central Australian terrane. Boundaries follow Shaw et al. (1995) and Hoatson et al. (1996).

properties.SOURCE: Bradshaw, B.E., Rollet, N., Totterdell, J.M., Borissova, I., 2003. A revised structural framework for frontier basins on the southern and southwestern Australian continental margin., Geoscience Australia. Record 2003/03

properties.DESCR: The ?Jurassic to Recent Zeewyck Sub-basin is a moderate size, deep water, frontier, strike-slip sub-basin within the Perth Basin containing at least 7 km of ?continental to marine strata.

properties.DESCR: The Early Permian to Recent Abrolhos Sub-basin is a mostly offshore, elongate, NNW-trending rift basin located in the northern Perth Basin and contains at least 7000 m of marine to continental sediments.

properties.SOURCE: Crostella, A., 2001. Geology and petroleum potential of the Abrolhos Sub-basin, Western Australia, Geological Survey of Western Australia. Report 75

properties.DESCR: The ?Permian to Cenozoic Houtman Sub-basin is a large, extensively faulted tectonic element of the Perth Basin located offshore on the southwestern Australian margin, containing up to 13 km of siliciclastic fluvial, deltaic and marine rocks.

properties.SOURCE: Crostella, A., 2001. Geology and petroleum potential of the Abrolhos Sub-basin, Western Australia, Geological Survey of Western Australia. Report 75

properties.NAME: Bunbury Trough
properties.DESCR: The Bunbury Trough is a north-south oriented extensional depocentre in the southern Perth Basin that contains in excess of 10,000 m of Cretaceous to Permian sedimentary rocks.
properties.COMMENTS: Contains predominantly Permian Cretaceous-age rocks with a thin Cenozoic cover.

properties.NAME: Eucla Basin
properties.DESCR: The Cainozoic Eucla Basin comprises a thin passive margin succession that extends from onshore Western Australia and South Australia to more than 500 km offshore, to the approximate foot-of-slope.
properties.COMMENTS: Onlapped by sediments of the Australian-Antarctic Basin at the present-day foot-of-slope.

properties.NAME: Darwin Shelf
properties.DESCR: The Darwin Shelf, located to the northeast of the Petrel Sub-basin on Australia's Northwest Shelf, is a regional structural high consisting of a thin succession of Jurassic to Cenozoic sedimentary rocks overlying basement.

properties.NAME: Peedamullah Shelf
properties.DESCR: The Peedamullah Shelf is a structural high which forms part of the inboard region of the Northern Carnarvon Basin. It is comprised of Ordovician to Holocene sedimentary rocks. The Flinders Fault System forms the northwestern boundary of the shelf .
